        <section>
            <title>Orbeon Forms in a Nutshell</title>
            <img src="../apps/doc/images/form-builder-400.png" class="ops-doc-image" alt="Screenshot of Orbeon Form Builder"/>
            <p>
                Welcome to the reference documentation for the Orbeon Forms platform!
            </p>
            <p>
                Orbeon Forms is your solution to build and deploy web forms:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Handles complex forms typical of the enterprise or government</li>
                <li>Works in standard web browsers</li>
                <li>Does not require any special client software or plugins</li>
                <li>Includes Form Builder, the web-based form authoring tool</li>
                <li>Is provided as open source under a business-friendly license</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Noteworthy features include:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>Fully interactive forms</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>As-you-type validation</li>
                        <li>Optional sections</li>
                        <li>Repeated sections</li>
                        <li>Up-to-date error summary</li>
                        <li>Based on Ajax technology</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Advanced form features</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Create PDF documents</li>
                        <li>Full internationalization</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>Advanced controls</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Auto-completion</li>
                        <li>Tab views</li>
                        <li>Dialogs</li>
                        <li>Trees</li>
                        <li>Menus</li>
                        <li>Programmable custom controls</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>An open solution</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Open source (LGPL)</li>
                        <li>Standards-based (XForms)</li>
                        <li>Commercially supported</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>A Solid technological foundation</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>User-friendly Ajax-based XForms engine supporting <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/xforms11/">XForms 1.1</a></li>
                        <li>The <a href="reference-xpl-pipelines">XPL engine</a>, a mature, high-performance XML pipeline engine for processing XML data</li>
                        <li>Form Runner, the Orbeon Forms runtime environment</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>
